Nigeria is just a little figures before hitting the 40,000- mark of COVID-19 cases. In the latest information disclosed by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Twitter, confirmed cases of the virus in the country are now 39977. 438 new cases were recorded just on Saturday and Lagos remains the epicentre of the pandemic. The new cases of COVID- 19 across the country spread thus: Lagos-123 Kaduna-50 Rivers-40 Edo-37 Adamawa-25 Oyo-20 Nasarawa-16 Osun-15 Enugu-15 FCT-14 Ekiti-13 Ondo-13 Ebonyi-11 Katsina-10 Abia-9 Delta-8 Kwara-4 Ogun-3 Cross River-3 Kano-3 Bauchi-3 Yobe-2 Sokoto-1 Niger-1  438 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Lagos-123Kaduna-50Rivers-40Edo-37Adamawa-25Oyo-20Nasarawa-16Osun-15Enugu-15FCT-14Ekiti-13Ondo-13Ebonyi-11Katsina-10Abia-9Delta-8Kwara-4Ogun-3Cross River-3Kano-3Bauchi-3Yobe-2Sokoto-1Niger-1 pic.twitter.com/QVEEvTktXP â€” NCDC (@NCDCgov) July 25, 2020  Out of the 39977 confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria, 16,948 patients have been discharged while 856 persons have died.